‚ÄºÔ∏èNORTHWEST BIPOC ENTERTAINERS‚ÄºÔ∏è

We are actively seeking talented BIPOC performers to bring beloved characters such as; Princess Tiana, Mulan, Mirabel, Jasmine, Moana, iconic Korean figures and more to life through engaging and authentic performances.

To our company representation matters! We are committed to celebrating the rich cultural heritage of these characters embodied by casting performers who reflect their backgrounds. Whether you're an experienced entertainer or a passionate newcomer, if you have a love for storytelling, performance, and creating magical moments for audiences of all ages, we invite you to join us in inspiring the next generation through inclusive and empowering portrayals.

Please PM Ever Enchanted Events or email everenchantedevent@gmail.com with a headshot, CV and a little about yourself and your backgroundü•∞‚≠êÔ∏è

üì¢Volunteers Wanted - Videographers! Liverpool Mystery Eventüì¢

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

What you'll get:

. Travel expenses covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

items.text:
Female Host ‚Äì Horror/True Crime Talk Show
Location: Burbank, California (or surrounding areas)

We are seeking a dynamic female host to join our on-camera team for a horror and true crime‚Äìfocused web series. This role requires someone with strong on-screen presence, a passion for horror, true crime, and the supernatural, and the ability to engage with both co-hosts and guests in a lively, authentic way.

Responsibilities:
 ‚Ä¢ Co-host alongside two main hosts during live-taped shows.
 ‚Ä¢ Contribute knowledge and insights on horror, true crime, and supernatural subjects.
 ‚Ä¢ Engage with guests, audience members, and co-hosts with energy and professionalism.
 ‚Ä¢ Help shape conversations that are informative, entertaining, and on-brand.

Requirements:
 ‚Ä¢ Female host talent based in Burbank, California, or nearby areas.
 ‚Ä¢ Strong knowledge of horror, true crime, and supernatural genres.
 ‚Ä¢ Confident on-camera presence and strong improvisational/conversational skills.
 ‚Ä¢ Ability to work collaboratively with other hosts.
 ‚Ä¢ Must be available for scheduled back-to-back tapings.
 ‚Ä¢ We are especially interested in candidates who already have a horror-style look or aesthetic that fits the tone of the show.

Compensation & Perks:
 ‚Ä¢ $500 per show.
 ‚Ä¢ We film two shows back-to-back per shoot day.
 ‚Ä¢ If selected, we will privately share details of the show and company.
 ‚Ä¢ All employees receive a quarterly bonus based on the show‚Äôs performance.
 ‚Ä¢ Small, tight-knit crew where every team member receives a percentage of the show‚Äôs profits.
 ‚Ä¢ Immediate hire.

How to Apply:

Please submit the following materials:
 ‚Ä¢ Headshot (highlighting your look and style).
 ‚Ä¢ Demo reel or on-camera sample (hosting, acting, or relevant video work).
 ‚Ä¢ Resume with relevant experience.
 ‚Ä¢ A brief note on why you‚Äôre passionate about horror/true crime/supernatural.

Submit to VCSales505@gmail.com

**Tanzp√§dagog:innen & Tanzlehrer:innen (m/w/d) gesucht**

**f√ºr verschiedene Tanzrichtungen ‚Äì Festanstellung oder auf Honorarbasis**

**üï∫ √úber uns**

Das **TanzHaus Erfurt** ist eines der gr√∂√üten Tanzstudios in Th√ºringen mit rund 1000 Mitgliedern. Unser Programm umfasst ein breites Spektrum von **Hip Hop, Commercial, Urban Contemporary** √ºber **Jazz, Modern Dance, Ballett** bis hin zu **Kindertanz, Fitness- und Paartanzkursen**. Mehrere Companies und Crews sind Teil unserer Schule.
Neben dem regul√§ren Unterricht sind wir Gastgeber der **Internationalen Erfurter Sommertanztage** und kooperieren mit Dozent:innen aus aller Welt.

Zur Verst√§rkung unseres Teams suchen wir engagierte **Tanzlehrer:innen und Tanzp√§dagog:innen** f√ºr verschiedene Stilrichtungen.

**üéØ Dein Profil**
* Du unterrichtest einen oder mehrere Tanzstile (z. B. **Hip Hop, Commercial, Jazz, Contemporary, Ballett, Kindertanz**).
* Du hast Freude an der Arbeit mit verschiedenen Altersgruppen (Kinder, Jugendliche, Erwachsene) verschiedener Level (Anf√§nger bis Fortgeschrittene).
* Du verf√ºgst √ºber Unterrichtserfahrung oder eine p√§dagogische Ausbildung im Tanz.
* Du hast vielleicht Erfahrung bei der Entwicklung von Wettkampf-Choreografien.
* Du bist zuverl√§ssig, teamorientiert und motiviert, **regelm√§√üig in Erfurt** zu unterrichten.

**üí° Wir bieten dir**
* **Mehrere feste Kurse pro Woche** ‚Äì mit Option auf Ausbau.
* M√∂glichkeit einer **Festanstellung** (Vollzeit, Teilzeit, Midi- oder Minijob) oder attraktiver Honorart√§tigkeit.
* Eine moderne k√ºnstlerische Tanzschule mit professionell ausgestatteten Studios.
* Ein tolles Team, was dich mit offenen Armen empf√§ngt.
* Eine lebendige Tanz-Community und Auftrittsm√∂glichkeiten bei Events & Projekten.
* Raum f√ºr deine Kreativit√§t und Unterst√ºtzung bei der Umsetzung eigener Ideen.

**üìç Standort**

**TanzHaus Erfurt ‚Äì im Herzen Th√ºringens, in der Mitte von Deutschland**
Zentrale Lage mit guter Erreichbarkeit (Leipzig, Halle, Jena, Weimar, Berlin, Frankfurt, Kassel, Hannover, G√∂ttingen, Coburg, Bamberg, N√ºrnberg).

**üì© Bewerbung**

üëâ Sende uns deine **kurze Vorstellung + Tanzvideo oder CV** an:
üìß info@tanzhaus-erfurt.de

Dance&Arts is growing, and we're looking for **passionate dance, drama, and arts instructors to join our team in Birmingham**! If you love inspiring young talents, we want to hear from you!

 

‚ú® We‚Äôre hiring for:

‚úÖ Dance (all styles)

‚úÖ Drama

‚úÖ Musical Theatre

‚úÖ Basic Gymnastics (mat-based only)

‚úÖ Arts & Crafts

 

üí∞ Pay: ¬£30 per hour

 

üì© How to Apply: Send your **Enhanced DBS & CV to ****teachers@dancearts-uk.com** with your preferred position in the subject line.

 

Join us in bringing creativity, movement, and inspiration to the next generation! üåü

items.text:
The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - 
https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

items.title: ‚ú®Hiring: Belly Dancer ‚ú®

items.text:
Hi everyone, I'm Deividas 30, Lithuanian.

Model | Performer | Wellness Professional
With over 50 professional photoshoots under my belt ‚Äî including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling ‚Äî I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset.

Link below intro video
https://drive.google.com/file/d/19OcejTSRFWF2ZmQxdeoF92CEF7TKKAdb/view?usp=drivesdk

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work.

Performance Skills
‚Ä¢ Aerial Acrobatics ‚Äî Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner‚ÄìIntermediate)
‚Ä¢ Contact Fire Staff ‚Äî Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Katana Wielding ‚Äî Intermediate 
‚Ä¢ Yoga ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Swimming ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Parkour - Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Dancing - non professional but confident dancer

I‚Äôm currently seeking freelance work as model/actor/performer and agency representation (available internationally). Open to test shoots, collaborations, and paid opportunities.

‚ú® Updated measurements (as of Sept 22, 2025):
Height: 195cm
Chest: 41
Waist: 32
Hips: 37.5
Neck: 16
Sleeve: 32 (81.5cm)
Inseam: 32 (81.5cm)
Outseam: 36.4 (92.3cm)
Shoulder Width: 19 (48.5cm)
Shoe: UK 10.5 (can do 10‚Äì11) | EU 44‚Äì46

üåç Based in London | Available worldwide

Professional Background
‚Ä¢ Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 12+ years of teaching experience.
‚Ä¢ Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance.

What Sets Me Apart
‚Ä¢ Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.
‚Ä¢ Holistic approach to self-regulation ‚Äî always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.
‚Ä¢ Highly motivated in building my craft and presence ‚Äî I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience reach and on-camera charisma.

Current Focus
Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance ‚Äî primarily in the UK (based in London ) but open to international projects. I‚Äôm committed to levelling up my skills, embracing bold creative challenges, and bringing exceptional authentic energy, professionalism, and reliability to every collaboration.

If you need anything else please let me know 

Kindest regards 
Deividas Juozapaviƒçius
+12022558377
Instagram: @deivjuo
YouTube: @deivjuo
TikTok: @deivjuo

‚Ä¢ Aerial Acrobatics ‚Äî Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner‚ÄìIntermediate)
‚Ä¢ Contact Fire Staff ‚Äî Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Katana Wielding ‚Äî Intermediate 
‚Ä¢ Yoga ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Swimming ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Parkour - Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Dancing - non professional but confident dancer

I‚Äôm currently seeking freelance work as model/actor/performer and agency representation (available internationally). Open to test shoots, collaborations, and paid opportunities.

‚ú® Updated measurements (as of Sept 22, 2025):
Height: 195cm
Chest: 41
Waist: 32
Hips: 37.5
Neck: 16
Sleeve: 32 (81.5cm)
Inseam: 32 (81.5cm)
Outseam: 36.4 (92.3cm)
Shoulder Width: 19 (48.5cm)
Shoe: UK 10.5 (can do 10‚Äì11) | EU 44‚Äì46

üåç Based in London | Available worldwide

Professional Background
‚Ä¢ Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 12+ years of teaching experience.
‚Ä¢ Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance.

What Sets Me Apart
‚Ä¢ Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.
‚Ä¢ Holistic approach to self-regulation ‚Äî always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.
‚Ä¢ Highly motivated in building my craft and presence ‚Äî I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience reach and on-camera charisma.

Current Focus
Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance ‚Äî primarily in the UK (based in London ) but open to international projects. I‚Äôm committed to levelling up my skills, embracing bold creative challenges, and bringing exceptional authentic energy, professionalism, and reliability to every collaboration.

If you need anything else please let me know 

Kindest regards 
Deividas Juozapaviƒçius

sharedPost.text:
Angela Boehm Casting is now looking for talent for a Promotional Video Shoot for 'OHIO JOBS'.

This project will be filming in October in Cleveland, OH, Columbus, OH, AND CINCINNATI, OH. (We have 18 Roles over 3 Different Cities).

Please read carefully below for details:

DETAILS:
- Project: 'OHIO JOBS' Promotional Shoot
- Project Location: Cleveland, OH (TBD) / Columbus, OH (TBD) / Cincinnati, OH (TBD)
- Date(s): October 7th / October 8th / October 9th / October 10th
- CALLBACK Date: Tuesday, September 30th (via Zoom)
- Rate: $500/10hr +20% per Session.
- Fitting Rate: $50/hr + 20% 
(Cincinnati Talent will fit on OCTOBER 6th. Columbus & Cleveland Talent will fit ON-SET)
- Usage: 2-Year Usage Buyout $2500 + 20% (Broadcast, Digital, Social, Print, OOH, Industrial)

WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR:
WE HAVE 18 ROLES OVER THE 3 OHIO CITIES FOR ALL AGES AND ETHNICITIES!!

Link to Roles & Cities they film: https://bit.ly/OhioJobsROLESandCITIES

SUBMISSION / AUDITION INSTRUCTIONS:
- Please email all auditions to: angela@angelaboehmcasting.com

- Deadline for Auditions is 9:00am on FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 26th.

- SUBJECT LINE: OHIO JOBS Audition / (Your Name)
- Please have a blank background (DO NOT film outside).
- Please slate at the end of the audition (Slate can be in a separate video).

Slate Requirements:
- Full Name
- Agent (Phone number if you do not have an Agent)
- Location (PLEASE SLATE IF YOU'RE WILLING TO WORK LOCAL IN MORE THAN ONE OF THE MENTIONED CITIES)
- Please include in your slate a close-up of BOTH of your hands, FRONT & BACK!
- PLEASE SLATE ANY CONFLICTS ON FILMING/FITTING/CALLBACK DATES
- Please send the audition via Dropbox Folder or via WeTransfer Link (PLEASE MAKE SURE WE HAVE PERMISSION TO OPEN YOUR FILE).

Click below for the Audition Sides:
Link to Sides: https://bit.ly/OhioJobsSIDES

Kind regards,
Angela Boehm Casting Team

PLEASE NOTE: This is just a submission. If you are booked, we will reach out to YOU.

items.text:
Hi Everyone!

I'm a student studying filmmaking at **Birmingham City University**, and for one of our assignments, we are creating a **short film** and are looking for actors.

The concept isn't decided yet, but we are deciding between two:
1. A past chess champion reminisces about his glory days and replays the match that he lost in which started his downfall.
2. A girl whose inner self is screaming at her to help, while she is sucked into her phone, a film themed on how addicted we are to our phones.

We have a Test Shoot Day on the 23rd of October, 9:00am-12:00pm, and the Shoot Day is on the 4th of November, 9:00am-4:00pm. Both are at Parkside Building, Birmingham City University.

As we are students, this will be unpaid, unfortunately. But this is a great opportunity for actors who are starting out and want to get something on their resumes. We will include you in the credits.

We will have more details before the shoot, so don't worry.

If you are interested, please send an email to this address: **maisie.condron@mail.bcu.ac.uk**

Please include this information:

- Name

- Age

- Sex

- Location

- A self-tape of any performance

We will also be having more films come up in the future, so if you don't fit any of the roles described, you can still send an application in!

Thank you!

Hi everyone, I'm Deividas 30, Lithuanian.

Model | Performer | Wellness Professional
With over 50 professional photoshoots under my belt ‚Äî including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling ‚Äî I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset.

Link below intro video
https://drive.google.com/file/d/19OcejTSRFWF2ZmQxdeoF92CEF7TKKAdb/view?usp=drivesdk

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work.

Performance Skills
‚Ä¢ Aerial Acrobatics ‚Äî Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner‚ÄìIntermediate)
‚Ä¢ Contact Fire Staff ‚Äî Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Katana Wielding ‚Äî Intermediate 
‚Ä¢ Yoga ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Swimming ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Parkour - Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Dancing - non professional but confident dancer

I‚Äôm currently seeking freelance work as model/actor/performer and agency representation (available internationally). Open to test shoots, collaborations, and paid opportunities.

üåç Based in London | Available worldwide

Professional Background
‚Ä¢ Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 12+ years of teaching experience.
‚Ä¢ Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance.

What Sets Me Apart
‚Ä¢ Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.
‚Ä¢ Holistic approach to self-regulation ‚Äî always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.
‚Ä¢ Highly motivated in building my craft and presence ‚Äî I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience reach and on-camera charisma.

Current Focus
Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance ‚Äî primarily in the UK (based in London ) but open to international projects. I‚Äôm committed to levelling up my skills, embracing bold creative challenges, and bringing exceptional authentic energy, professionalism, and reliability to every collaboration.

If you need anything else please let me know 

Kindest regards 
Deividas Juozapaviƒçius

items.text:
Hi Everyone!

I'm a student studying filmmaking at **Birmingham City University**, and for one of our assignments, we are creating a **short film** and are looking for actors.

The concept isn't decided yet, but we are deciding between two:
1. A past chess champion reminisces about his glory days and replays the match that he lost in which started his downfall.
2. A girl whose inner self is screaming at her to help, while she is sucked into her phone, a film themed on how addicted we are to our phones.

We have a Test Shoot Day on the 23rd of October, 9:00am-12:00pm, and the Shoot Day is on the 4th of November, 9:00am-4:00pm. Both are at Parkside Building, Birmingham City University.

As we are students, this will be unpaid, unfortunately. But this is a great opportunity for actors who are starting out and want to get something on their resumes. We will include you in the credits.

We will have more details before the shoot, so don't worry.

If you are interested, please send an email to this address: **maisie.condron@mail.bcu.ac.uk**

Please include this information:

- Name

- Age

- Sex

- Location

- A self-tape of any performance

We will also be having more films come up in the future, so if you don't fit any of the roles described, you can still send an application in!

Thank you!

sharedPost.text:
The Foundry Acting Studio

Where Professional Training Meets Real Opportunity

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we believe every actor deserves a world class education without barriers, hidden costs, or false promises.

Our curriculum‚Ä¶. built and refined over six years,  is internationally recognised, exceeding Spotlight‚Äôs accreditation requirements by more than three times. We are Spotlight approved, SAG recognised, and currently in talks with other major organisations worldwide. Our work is supported by acclaimed writers, directors, and actors connected to some of the most influential platforms in the industry.

What makes us different:
 ‚Ä¢ World Class Curriculum: Designed to equal the top schools in the world, yet offered at a fraction of the cost.
 ‚Ä¢ No Hidden Tiers or Costs: Every actor receives the same training. There are no ‚Äúhigher levels,‚Äù upsells, or paywalls. Your talent is never defined by your wallet.
 ‚Ä¢ Personal Coaching: We keep classes small, so every actor is seen, heard, and individually assessed with hands on guidance.
 ‚Ä¢ No Agency Agenda: We are not an agency. You will never pay us for a promise of representation. Our focus is training and opportunity, not commission.
 ‚Ä¢ Industry Films: We are the only UK studio guaranteeing work by producing industry standard films with RED and ARRI cameras‚Ä¶. work that goes directly on your Spotlight profile.
 ‚Ä¢ Equality & Integrity

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we believe in building the industry, not dividing it. For that reason, we do not accept students who are currently in the middle of a paid term with another school or who are tied to an agency that is directly run by that same school. We respect the work of fellow coaches and do not believe in poaching actors away from their commitments.

Once an actor has completed their term elsewhere and is no longer represented under an agency attached to another school, they are welcome to join us for a fresh start. This ensures absolute fairness, integrity, and clarity for everyone involved.

Because The Foundry is not an agency, your place with us is never tied to representation. When you train here, your development is entirely about your craft. If you do not currently have an agent, our team will guide you toward finding one that best suits your path, independent, professional representation that has nothing to do with paying for classes.

We believe this creates a healthier, more transparent industry for all‚Ä¶ actors, coaches, and agencies alike.

 ‚Ä¢ Accessibility: Whether you are working full-time, on benefits, retired, or just beginning your journey, our training is affordable and inclusive. Discounts are available for civil servants.
 ‚Ä¢ Expanding Opportunities: Teen classes are launching soon, and new locations are opening across the UK.

Our Philosophy

When you walk through our doors, you are not a number, not a ‚Äúpound sign,‚Äù and never a currency. You are an actor, with equal right to professional training, opportunity, and growth.

At The Foundry, we believe in community. We believe in supporting fellow actors, fellow coaches, headshot photographers, showreel specialists, fight choreographers, and everyone who contributes to the craft. Together, we build the industry.

Ready to Join?

Direct message us today for full details on class times, dates, and locations near you. Step into a studio that is reshaping the future of acting in the UK and beyond.

The Foundry Acting Studio
Professional. Inclusive. Respected. Recognised

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall
Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 
Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.
Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 
The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

There has never been a better time for older performers to return to the industry. Right now, there‚Äôs a huge demand for actors over 50.If you‚Äôve taken a break  whether to raise a family, pursue another career, or simply step away for a while  this is the moment to come back. As you get older, there‚Äôs less competition, and the life experience you‚Äôve gained only strengthens your craft.

Sometimes that time away gives you exactly what you need to succeed when you return: perspective, resilience, and real-world skills that shine on screen and stage.

Remember  there‚Äôs a role for every age, and the industry is waiting for you.
#marksummers #marksummerscasting #castingdirector #olderwiserstronger #actors #castingcall

topComments.text: I've stepped my toe in at 46 and had a ball. Looking for more experience if you know of any particular castings for over 40s. Kindest regards x

The amazing JODIE STEELE is in the house this Sunday!

Our Associates Day is open to EVERYONE, ages 6-20

You do not need to be represented by us or looking for rep by us. 
Open to any performers with different agents. 
We love to share our skills, our industry friends, our experience & knowledge with all performers. 

You do not even need to be looking for an agent at all!
These days are great fun, a chance to workshop your skills, gain valuable feedback and meet new people!

Dance Audition Workshop
Acting Through Song
Ensemble Workshop
Monologues
Audition Technique

In Hove, an hour from central London on the train, just a few spaces left, book in now!

Movietime September 2025, The Third

EINE WARMHERZIGE STORY ≈∞BER BR√úDER UND EIN NEUES MAGISCHES SCHULJAHR STARTET

Die zweite Septemberh√§lfte bringt nicht nur Leonardo Di Caprio zur√ºck ins Kino (Stadtkino Center Laa), sondern es beginnt ein neues Jahr mit der SCHULE DER MAGISCHEN TIERE 4 (Babylon Kino, Filmb√ºhne Waidhofen/Ybbs).

Einem ungleichen Br√ºderpaar begegnet man in GANZER HALBER BRUDER (Stadtkino Horn), wobei wir mit dem Hauptdarsteller Christoph Maria Herbst ein paar Worte plaudern durften.

Der √ñ Film hat weitere Highlights parat, wo wir in der Sendung auch 2 Interviews mit den RegisseurInnen f√ºhren konnten. NARBEN EINES PUTSCHES oder HOW TO BE NORMAL AND THE ODDNESS OF THE OTHER WORLD (Kronenkino Mistelbach).

In den Lichtspielen Gf√∂hl gibt es Ende September einen besonderen Event mit dem Filmarchiv Austria und wir trafen eine Zeitzeugin, die im Sitzendorfer Kino noch die Sissi-Filme gesehen hat.

Abgerundet wird das Kinomagazin musikalisch in Memoriam Robert Redford, in dem wir Songs und Themes seiner besten Filme pr√§sentieren.

Mittwoch 24.09.2025 von 17 bis 19h EXKLUSIV auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

items.text:
Dear Actors, 

Join me Saturday for a free 75-minute ONLINE class: HOW TO CHOOSE A MONOLOGUE FOR ANY AUDITION.  Participants can read or perform monologues for feedback  and I cover a LOT about choosing monologues, including . . .

‚Ä¢ How to find material that‚Äôs great for you
‚Ä¢ Where to look
‚Ä¢ How to recognize good material
‚Ä¢ Choosing well for specific kinds of auditions
‚Ä¢ Building a killer repertoire
‚Ä¢ Effective cutting and editing
‚Ä¢ When and when not to do overdone monologues
‚Ä¢ The ‚ÄúHello, This Is Me‚Äù monologue and why it‚Äôs so incredibly valuable for auditioning actors

To reserve, email classes@monologueaudition.com

**Can't do this one? Email classes@monologueaudition.com to join my list and hear about next classes and free events :) **

You can also visit my website, MonologueAudition.com for Monologue FAQ, Monday Morning Monologues (free feedback on Mondays), a short film about how I teach monologues, and much more :) 

~Karen 

KAREN KOHLHAAS is a director and founding ensemble member of the Atlantic Theater Company and senior teacher at the Atlantic Acting School. She teaches her own online classes in monologues, cold reading, scene study, and directing, and is the author of The Monologue Audition: A Practical Guide for Actors (recommended by Helen Mirren in her Master Class on acting, and a Backstage must-read); and How to Choose a Monologue for Any Audition. She was named Best NYC Monologue Teacher and Best NYC Cold Reading Teacher by Backstage readers.

**Can't do this one? Email classes@monologueaudition.com to join my list and hear about next classes and free events :) **

You can also visit my website, MonologueAudition.com for Monologue FAQ, Monday Morning Monologues (free feedback on Mondays), a short film about how I teach monologues, and much more :) 

~Karen 

KAREN KOHLHAAS is a director and founding ensemble member of the Atlantic Theater Company and senior teacher at the Atlantic Acting School. She teaches her own online classes in monologues, cold reading, scene study, and directing, and is the author of The Monologue Audition: A Practical Guide for Actors (recommended by Helen Mirren in her Master Class on acting, and a Backstage must-read); and How to Choose a Monologue for Any Audition. She was named Best NYC Monologue Teacher and Best NYC Cold Reading Teacher by Backstage readers.

CASTING CALL

We‚Äôre looking for a female actor to join us this December for our RAPUNZEL pantomime (school tour). 

We‚Äôre casting either of the following parts, with our existing performer playing the opposite role. 

- Rapunzel (lead)
- Gothel (villain)

Last year was our best selling tour - but we hope to beat that this year! Because it‚Äôs schools, the shows are weekday mornings and early afternoons, so you‚Äôll have your evenings and weekends free. The performances are in the Norfolk, Suffolk and Cambridge area. 

We‚Äôre currently offering a minimum of ¬£870 - which will go up as we get more bookings in + travel expenses. 
The tour spans from 1st - 19th December 2025. 
Aiming to start weekly rehearsals asap - in Hunstanton (PE36). These are unpaid but we keep them as flexible as possible.

This will be our thirteenth panto tour, and we‚Äôve built up a good name in the area, with schools booking us year after year (even before we announce the title!) We pride ourselves on being a warm, friendly, but professional company.

If interested, please get in touch for further details - either by a PM on here, or via email - purple-dreams@hotmail.co.uk - I‚Äôm looking forward to hearing from (some of) you üôÇ

Many thanks
Tobias Nicholls
Creative Director 
Purple Dreams Productions

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

Hi everyone, I'm Deividas 30, Lithuanian.

Model | Performer | Wellness Professional
With over 50 professional photoshoots under my belt ‚Äî including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling ‚Äî I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset.

Link below intro video
https://drive.google.com/file/d/19OcejTSRFWF2ZmQxdeoF92CEF7TKKAdb/view?usp=drivesdk

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work.

Performance Skills
‚Ä¢ Aerial Acrobatics ‚Äî Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner‚ÄìIntermediate)
‚Ä¢ Contact Fire Staff ‚Äî Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Katana Wielding ‚Äî Intermediate 
‚Ä¢ Yoga ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Swimming ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Parkour - Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Dancing - non professional but confident dancer

I‚Äôm currently seeking freelance work as model/actor/performer and agency representation (available internationally). Open to test shoots, collaborations, and paid opportunities.

‚ú® Updated measurements (as of Sept 22, 2025):
Height: 195cm
Chest: 41
Waist: 32
Hips: 37.5
Neck: 16
Sleeve: 32 (81.5cm)
Inseam: 32 (81.5cm)
Outseam: 36.4 (92.3cm)
Shoulder Width: 19 (48.5cm)
Shoe: UK 10.5 (can do 10‚Äì11) | EU 44‚Äì46

üåç Based in London | Available worldwide

Professional Background
‚Ä¢ Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 12+ years of teaching experience.
‚Ä¢ Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance.

What Sets Me Apart
‚Ä¢ Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.
‚Ä¢ Holistic approach to self-regulation ‚Äî always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.
‚Ä¢ Highly motivated in building my craft and presence ‚Äî I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience reach and on-camera charisma.

Current Focus
Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance ‚Äî primarily in the UK (based in London ) but open to international projects. I‚Äôm committed to levelling up my skills, embracing bold creative challenges, and bringing exceptional authentic energy, professionalism, and reliability to every collaboration.

If you need anything else please let me know 

Kindest regards 
Deividas Juozapaviƒçius
+12022558377
Instagram: @deivjuo
YouTube: @deivjuo
TikTok: @deivjuo

items.text:
This is for those who seek an intimate unique experience‚Ä¶

The Shop For Mortals and Fools
Opening soon in Central
london. Only for select customers.

Old relics, curious finds, hidden trinkets, and heirlooms ‚Äì treasures that whisper forgotten stories. In this enigmatic shop, a select audience is invited to an exclusive preview of its mysterious collection.

Inspired by Euripides‚Äô The Bacchae, this bold production delves into one of the greatest tragedies ever written, weaving an original and compelling narrative that explores power, vengeance. The production transforms a disused space into an atmospheric shop, a mythic world where gods, mortals, and unsuspecting customers collide in the voice of a woman.

Mystery awaits. Don‚Äôt miss out ‚Äì join the curious and fools, book your tickets today! https://www.tickettailor.com/events/theshopformortalsandallfools

And get this exclusive discount: F00ls100 or F00ls200

Co-Produced by Stanley Arts  photo with Kate Webster and photo by James Lawson Stanley ArtsKate WebsterJames Lawson@

This is for those who seek an intimate unique experience‚Ä¶

The Shop For Mortals and Fools
Opening soon in Central
london. Only for select customers.

Old relics, curious finds, hidden trinkets, and heirlooms ‚Äì treasures that whisper forgotten stories. In this enigmatic shop, a select audience is invited to an exclusive preview of its mysterious collection.

Inspired by Euripides‚Äô The Bacchae, this bold production delves into one of the greatest tragedies ever written, weaving an original and compelling narrative that explores power, vengeance. The production transforms a disused space into an atmospheric shop, a mythic world where gods, mortals, and unsuspecting customers collide in the voice of a woman.

Mystery awaits. Don‚Äôt miss out ‚Äì join the curious and fools, book your tickets today! https://www.tickettailor.com/events/theshopformortalsandallfools

And get this exclusive discount: F00ls100 or F00ls200

**$500 Finders Fee: Have You Been Ghosted By Your Husband Or Wife? (Docu-Series Casting)**

An acclaimed television production company and a major cable network are actively searching for women and men whose spouse has suddenly and mysteriously vanished, without warning, without explanation, and with no way to contact them. If you are still *legally married* but don‚Äôt know *where *your spouse is, you don‚Äôt have a clear explanation or *‚Äúwhy‚Äù* they left, or *how* to reach them, *we want to hear your story for a bold and empowering new series.*

**$500 Referral Fee: **Do You Know Someone? Share their information with us or simply have them tell us you referred them! Finders fee is paid IF referral is selected for production. 

*Selected for series candidates are compensated for taking part as well as receive expert help in tracking down their missing spouse, rebuilding their lives and finding closure. *

**To apply, please email: ****[casting@bodegapictures.com](mailto:casting@bodegapictures.com)****, **or visit: https://abandonedspouseshortapp.castingcrane.com/

items.text:
Hello all, this is another post for a different student film happening on Auraria Campus. I am not involved in this one, I am posting to this group for the producer since he is not on Facebook. So if you are interested in this one please contact the producer. 

Producer- Brennan Jones bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Production Title- The Cost of Greed 

Production Dates- Exact dates are not set but filming will be in October 

Logline- Peter and Henry are sent on a treasure hunt to a house that is believed to be abandoned. Where they then discover it's not a treasure hunt after all and they must face their greed. Either take the treasure or leave empty handed. 

Peter (19-25) Male 

Peter has a moral compass that he deals with during this film. He wants to do the right thing and in the end that pays off for him. 

Henry (19-25) Male 

Henry is a billionaire with no need for more money, however that does not stop him from thinking he needs more. He is corrupt and in the end karma gets to him. 

Audition Dates- September 18th-September 29th

Audition Location- Email-Self Tape

This is a student film for a final project therefore this film is non paid and non union.

Contact Email- bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Must contact the producer to be consider for the role. Once you contact Brennan he will send you the audition material.

The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

items.text:
# **Casting Call: Student Short Film **

We are currently casting for two lead roles in our upcoming short film, filming at the beginning of November.

**Logline:**

A family gathers for dinner at a tarot-themed restaurant, but as the cards are drawn, buried secrets surface‚Äîturning a simple night out into an inescapable reckoning.

# **Roles:**

**ROBERT** (Male, 45‚Äì55)

The head of the family and a successful businesman. Robert appears to have it all ‚Äî the career, the looks, the picture-perfect family. But beneath his composed, masculine exterior lies a man quietly suffocating, worn down by a life built on duty and expectations rather than desire. Over the course of the dinner, the cracks in his fa√ßade widen, pushing him toward a mental and emotional breaking point. This role requires strong range, balancing authority, charisma, and the slow unraveling into vulnerability and collapse.

**MADISON** (Female, 18‚Äì25)

The golden girl and youngest in the family, Madison is gorgeous, accomplished, and everyone‚Äôs clear favorite. On the surface, she embodies perfection ‚Äî beauty, brains, and charm ‚Äî but beneath that polish lies a calculating edge. She knows how to use her ‚Äúpretty privilege‚Äù to her advantage, and she‚Äôs smart enough to make it her power. Yet the flawless image she projects is fragile, threatened by a secret that could shatter it in an instant. The role calls for a nuanced performance that blends charm, wit, and the darker undertones of ambition and self-preservation.

# **Shoot Details:**
* **Filming Dates:** 3rd to 6th November (4 consecutive days)
* **Time:** 9:00 AM ‚Äì 7:00 PM daily
* **Location:** W5 3HN (West London)
* **Rehearsal & Table Read **prior to filming days
* **Payment:** ¬£400 total per role

# **How to Apply:**

If you‚Äôre interested, please **fill out the form below** and we‚Äôll send you script excerpts for a self-tape.

[https://forms.gle/N4NPWpKDLSWnZAD46](https://forms.gle/N4NPWpKDLSWnZAD46) 

We are really excited to make this project happen and would love to have you on board! 

Thanks,
Liza

Synopsis - Dennis Le'Claire, 'World's Greatest Actor', is missing - and it's opening night! It's a theatre production's worst nightmare, that is until Sebastian Paris, 'World's Greatest Understudy', arrives on the scene. But all is not as it seems, as talks of foul play begin to spread.

In this force of farce, take a peek behind the curtain at scheming stage hands, devious directors, and preposterous playwrights.

__________________

A big thanks to those who came to our first set of auditions on Monday - it was fantastic to see the characters come to life and you all brought your A-game. We're looking forward to the rest of the week!

Audition information

sharedPost.text:
The Foundry Acting Studio

Where Professional Training Meets Real Opportunity

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we believe every actor deserves a world class education without barriers, hidden costs, or false promises.

Our curriculum‚Ä¶. built and refined over six years,  is internationally recognised, exceeding Spotlight‚Äôs accreditation requirements by more than three times. We are Spotlight approved, SAG recognised, and currently in talks with other major organisations worldwide. Our work is supported by acclaimed writers, directors, and actors connected to some of the most influential platforms in the industry.

What makes us different:
 ‚Ä¢ World Class Curriculum: Designed to equal the top schools in the world, yet offered at a fraction of the cost.
 ‚Ä¢ No Hidden Tiers or Costs: Every actor receives the same training. There are no ‚Äúhigher levels,‚Äù upsells, or paywalls. Your talent is never defined by your wallet.
 ‚Ä¢ Personal Coaching: We keep classes small, so every actor is seen, heard, and individually assessed with hands on guidance.
 ‚Ä¢ No Agency Agenda: We are not an agency. You will never pay us for a promise of representation. Our focus is training and opportunity, not commission.
 ‚Ä¢ Industry Films: We are the only UK studio guaranteeing work by producing industry standard films with RED and ARRI cameras‚Ä¶. work that goes directly on your Spotlight profile.
 ‚Ä¢ Equality & Integrity

At The Foundry Acting Studio, we believe in building the industry, not dividing it. For that reason, we do not accept students who are currently in the middle of a paid term with another school or who are tied to an agency that is directly run by that same school. We respect the work of fellow coaches and do not believe in poaching actors away from their commitments.

Once an actor has completed their term elsewhere and is no longer represented under an agency attached to another school, they are welcome to join us for a fresh start. This ensures absolute fairness, integrity, and clarity for everyone involved.

Because The Foundry is not an agency, your place with us is never tied to representation. When you train here, your development is entirely about your craft. If you do not currently have an agent, our team will guide you toward finding one that best suits your path, independent, professional representation that has nothing to do with paying for classes.

We believe this creates a healthier, more transparent industry for all‚Ä¶ actors, coaches, and agencies alike.

 ‚Ä¢ Accessibility: Whether you are working full-time, on benefits, retired, or just beginning your journey, our training is affordable and inclusive. Discounts are available for civil servants.
 ‚Ä¢ Expanding Opportunities: Teen classes are launching soon, and new locations are opening across the UK.

Our Philosophy

When you walk through our doors, you are not a number, not a ‚Äúpound sign,‚Äù and never a currency. You are an actor, with equal right to professional training, opportunity, and growth.

At The Foundry, we believe in community. We believe in supporting fellow actors, fellow coaches, headshot photographers, showreel specialists, fight choreographers, and everyone who contributes to the craft. Together, we build the industry.

Ready to Join?

Direct message us today for full details on class times, dates, and locations near you. Step into a studio that is reshaping the future of acting in the UK and beyond.

The Foundry Acting Studio
Professional. Inclusive. Respected. Recognised
